                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17310115-63-defend361 t17310115-63-defloc316"></join>, was indicted for that he <rs id="t17310115-63-off317" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17310115-63-off317" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310115-63-off317" type="offenceSubcategory" value="extortion"></interp>
               being an ill disposed Person, and greedy of wicked Lucre, after the 1st of June 1723, that is to say, on the <rs id="t17310115-63-cd318" type="crimeDate">24th of November 1730</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17310115-63-off317 t17310115-63-cd318"></join>, the Laws and Statutes of this Realm not esteeming, did knowingly, wickedly, and feloniously send a Letter sign'd Armstrong, to 
                     
                        <persName id="t17310115-63-victim363" type="victimName">
                           William 
                           Gaughton 
                        <interp inst="t17310115-63-victim363" type="surname" value="Gaughton"></interp>
